modules.description: The module offers no functionality, as it consists solely of an empty child module with no defined types or operations. There are no data types or functions available for use or manipulation. As a result, no meaningful operations or transformations can be performed within this module. It serves no practical purpose in a codebase.

This module implements custom syntax extensions for OCaml using PPX, providing functions to read and transform source files. It works with OCaml's abstract syntax trees (ASTs), hashtables of file contents, and location information from `Ppxlib`. Concrete operations include expanding expressions and structures during compilation, creating formatted demo strings with source locations, and retrieving stored file data.
